<p><h2>Songwritting</h2></p>
<p>Songwritting is the first step in the song production. You can start with just a groove, melody, or even just lyrics! In this stage you will start to choose the structure 
    of your song, you will choose what mood you want for your song, the message you are trying to tell, and this will begin giving your song life! There are many diffrent techniques to start this process, check out <a href="https://www.masterclass.com/articles/songwriting-tips-techniques-for-writing-memorable-songs">
        <em>Song Writing Masterclass.</em> </a> </p>
    <p><h2>Arranging</h2></p>
    <p>Arranging is the next step  after you've completeted your song writting process! Now it's time focus on pin-pointing your exact structuring of your song.
       This is where you need to focus on whether the song works on it's own, make sure it has a good legnth, and organize all of the instruments together.
    There are three types of arrangments flow, voicing, and the mix. For more indepth information on the three types of three arrangments, check out <a href="https://hyperbits.com/the-art-of-arranging-a-song/">
        <em>The art of arranging.</em></a>
    </a>  </p>
